28 /// \brief Streaming object file generation interface.
29 ///
30 /// This class provides an implementation of the MCStreamer interface which is
31 /// suitable for use with the assembler backend. Specific object file formats
32 /// are expected to subclass this interface to implement directives specific
33 /// to that file format or custom semantics expected by the object writer
34 /// implementation.
35 class MCObjectStreamer : public MCStreamer {
36  MCAssembler *Assembler;
37  MCSectionData *CurSectionData;
38  MCSectionData::iterator CurInsertionPoint;
39  bool EmitEHFrame;
40  bool EmitDebugFrame;
41  SmallVector<MCSymbolData *, 2> PendingLabels;
42 
43  virtual void EmitInstToData(const MCInst &Inst, const MCSubtargetInfo&) = 0;
44  void EmitCFIStartProcImpl(MCDwarfFrameInfo &Frame) override;
45  void EmitCFIEndProcImpl(MCDwarfFrameInfo &Frame) override;
46 
47  // If any labels have been emitted but not assigned fragments, ensure that
48  // they get assigned, either to F if possible or to a new data fragment.
49  void flushPendingLabels(MCFragment *F);
50 
51 protected:
52  MCObjectStreamer(MCContext &Context, MCAsmBackend &TAB, raw_ostream &_OS,
53  MCCodeEmitter *_Emitter);
54  MCObjectStreamer(MCContext &Context, MCAsmBackend &TAB, raw_ostream &_OS,
55  MCCodeEmitter *_Emitter, MCAssembler *_Assembler);
56  ~MCObjectStreamer();
57 
58 public:
59  /// state management
60  void reset() override;
61 
62  /// Object streamers require the integrated assembler.
63  bool isIntegratedAssemblerRequired() const override { return true; }
64 
65  MCSymbolData &getOrCreateSymbolData(const MCSymbol *Symbol) {
66  return getAssembler().getOrCreateSymbolData(*Symbol);
67  }
68  void EmitFrames(MCAsmBackend *MAB);
69  void EmitCFISections(bool EH, bool Debug) override;
70 
71 protected:
72  MCSectionData *getCurrentSectionData() const {
73  return CurSectionData;
74  }
75 
76  MCFragment *getCurrentFragment() const;
77 
78  void insert(MCFragment *F) {
79  flushPendingLabels(F);
80  CurSectionData->getFragmentList().insert(CurInsertionPoint, F);
81  F->setParent(CurSectionData);
82  }
83 
84  /// Get a data fragment to write into, creating a new one if the current
85  /// fragment is not a data fragment.
86  MCDataFragment *getOrCreateDataFragment();
87 
88 public:
89  void visitUsedSymbol(const MCSymbol &Sym) override;
90 
91  MCAssembler &getAssembler() { return *Assembler; }
